                  "input": "Concept: {{ trigger[\"nodeText\"] }}\nNew stage: {{ a0000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001[\"result\"] }}",
                  "prompt": "You are the Pipeline Orchestrator for a math game studio. A game concept has just advanced to a new pipeline stage. Write a concise 2-sentence summary of what this stage means for the concept and what the next action should be. Be specific about the stage name and what work is required.\n\nPipeline stages reference:\n- stage-spec: Write the full Game Experience Spec (core fantasy, core action, natural ceiling)\n- stage-precheck: Run Pre-Build Excellence Check (player motivation, memorable moments, mastery layers, decision quality, friction risks)\n- stage-delight: Run Delight Gate assessment — PASS or FAIL with reason\n- stage-design: Run Design Checks (fantasy integrity, satisfaction loop, consequence quality, replay variation)\n- stage-overlap: Run Skill & Overlap Review (family assignment, CCSS alignment, overlap analysis)\n- stage-gono: Render final GO / NO-GO Decision with rationale\n- stage-p1: Build P1 prototype — define success criteria and begin development\n- stage-p2a: P2A — add pressure & progression layer\n- stage-p2b: P2B — content expansion and difficulty ramp\n- stage-p3: P3 — feel, polish, and particle/feedback pass\n- stage-p4: P4 — full content + scaffolding\n- stage-p5: P5 — meta, flair, release polish"
                }
              }
            }
